<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Joint written evidence from Avincis Group, Bristow Helicopters Limited and CHC Helicopter (HCS0001)</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Joint written evidence from Avincis Group, Bristow Helicopters Limited and CHC Helicopter (HCS0001)</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; margin-left:0pt"><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:462.1pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Executive summary</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">This is a joint submission from the three main operators of helicopter services in the UK North Sea – </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Bond Offshore Helicopters (part of the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Avincis Group</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, Bristow Helicopters Limited and CHC Helicopter. We welcome this inquiry as an important opportunity to discuss and assess the safety of helicopter operations in the North Sea.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> Our thoughts remain with those affected by </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">recen</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">t helicopter accidents in the U</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">K.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">As operators, our duty above all else is to provide the safest possible operating environment for our crews and passengers as we contribute to a secure and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">productive offshore oil </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">and</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">gas industry. All three operators are dedicated to safety – not only independently, as commercial organisations driving quality for our customers through innovation, but also increasingly in collaboration.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Potential areas for improvement include a move to one set of high standards and more common audit processes. Whilst standards and audit processes are set by our customers - UK North Sea oil and gas companies - with the best of safety intentions, a more joined-up approach would improve clarity and reduce complexity.  The UK </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Civil Aviation Authority (</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">CAA</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> is centrally positioned to be able to help drive this effort.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Another example of where the UK CAA could contribute to driving standards further still is through building upon the already </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">valuable work of its Helicopter Scientific </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Research Management Committee.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The operators have </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">established </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">a Joint Operators Review (JOR) Working Group. The Group has a mandate from</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, and the involvement of,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> each operator’s CEO to recommend and drive improvement and share best practice. Once the first tranche of prioritised work is complete, the Group will consider the benefits of increasing further the engagement with</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> helicopter manufacturers (or</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Original Equipment Manufacturers - </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">OEMs</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, oil and gas customers, regulators and others so that together we may continue to raise standards</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p></td></tr></table><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 16.81pt; padding-left:4.49pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Overview </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">1.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">In its Terms of Reference for this inquiry, the Committee makes reference to the ‘industry’ involved in the provision of helicopter flights in the UK North Sea. This industry includes helicopter manufacturers, helicopter operators and the energy companies whose staff and contractors travel between the mainland and offshore installations. The industry works together on safety. This submission represents the collective views of the industry’s three main helicopter operators:</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 48.76pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Avincis Group: </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">a UK-</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">based company that operates out of 295 bases in 10 countries. Under the Bond Air Services and Bond Offshore subsidiaries, Avincis provides aerial services for mission critical and blue light services around the world including medical emergencies, civil protection, search and rescue, fire</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">fighting, coast and city surveillance and energy support services including serving oil rigs in the North Sea</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 48.76pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Bristow Helicopters Limited: </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Bristow has been providing helicopter services to governments and the worldwide offshore energy business for over 60 years. Bristow Helicopters Limited is part of Bristow Group Inc, an international company that adopted the Bristow name. Bristow operates over 400 aircraft around the world, and</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, as well as serving the energy industry, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">operate</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">s </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">search and rescue </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">services </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">in the UK. </span></li></ul><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 56.7pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 48.76pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">CHC Helicopter: </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">with a history reaching back to helicopter services established in the 1940s, CHC </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">specialises </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">in transportation to oil and gas platforms, search and rescue services, and helicopter maintenance and overhaul. CHC has two divisions: CHC Helicopter Services and Heli-One (a helicopter maintenance, repair and overhaul business). CHC operates </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">about 240</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> helicopters in 30 countries around the world.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">1.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Worldwide</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, combined</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, the three operators employ </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">over 10,000 people</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. In 2012, they carried</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> around 3 million </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">passengers using a fleet of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">nearly 1,000</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> helicopters. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">1.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">In the UK, the operators together employ </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">almost 2,000 </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">people. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">In 2012, they carried over half a million </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">passengers to installations in the North Sea </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">with a combined </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">UK fleet of over 80 helicopters. Over the period from 1981 to 2010, there were almost 3 million flight hours in the UK Continental Shelf sector of the North Sea with over 54 million passengers carried. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 16.81pt; padding-left:4.49pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Safety in offshore helicopter operations</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">2.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">As operators, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">it is </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">our duty above all else is to provide the safest possible operating environment for our crews and passengers. All three operators are dedicated to safety – not only independently, as commercial organisations driving quality </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">and safety </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">for our customers through innovation, but also increasingly in collaboration. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">2.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Notwithstanding our collective commitment to safety, the North Sea oil and gas industry operates in a challenging environment and there are many inherent risks. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Aberdeen is home to the largest helicopter operation in the world and is considered one of the safest. A recent study commissioned by the UK Offshore Oil and Gas Industry Association Limited</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> found that for the period from 1995 to 2010, the safety record of helicopter operations in the UK Continental Shelf compared favourably with other operations in the North Sea and those elsewhere in the world. The following table compares the global fatal and non-fatal accident rates of UK Continental Shelf helicopter operations from 1995 to 2010 with all North Sea and worldwide operations, based on 100,000 flying hours.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; margin-left:15.9pt"><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-